{
  "texts": [
    "Theorem 2].",
    "We use the definitions of F, V ± in (2.7),(2.8), and let F i denote the i th coordinate of F and similarly for V ±.",
    "With this notation, assumptions (A1)-(A5) from [53, Theorem 2] can be written:(i) If ξ = 0, and b δ < δ+ν µ, then x 1 is locally asymptotically stable if R 0 ( b δ, 0) < 1, and unstable if R 0 ( b δ, 0) > 1.",
    "(ii) If ξ = 0, and b δ > δ+ν µ, then x 2 is locally asymptotically stable if R 0 ( δ+ν µ, b δ -δ+ν µ) < 1, and unstable if R 0 ( δ+ν µ, b δ -δ+ν µ) > 1.",
    "(iii) If ξ ∈ (0, 1], we write x 3 = (0, 0, s 3, 0, s * 3, 0)."
  ]
}